members.name: Dr. S. Nain
members.title: Veterinarian
members.about: Dr. Nain is working at Taylor Veterinary Clinic since May, 2012. Dr. Nain is one of the highly qualified Veterinarian, finished his PhD from University of Saskatchewan in 2008. Subsequently he worked for two years at Western College of Veterinary Medicine in Saskatoon and one year at University College of Veterinary Medicine, University of Calgary. Dr Nain has extensive experience in avian (Birds) health, toxicology and emergency medicine.

members.name: Dr. S. Arya
members.title: Veterinarian
members.about: Dr. Arya is working at Taylor Veterinary Clinic since May, 2012. Dr. Arya finished her MSc in Animal Nutrition from University of Saskatchewan in 2010. Dr. Arya volunteered at various veterinary facilities across western Canada in Lethbridge and Calgary before moving to Red Deer. Dr. Arya has special interest in preventive medicine, surgery and pet nutrition.

members.name: Dr. P. Kaakee
members.title: Veterinarian
members.about: Dr. Pam graduated from the Ontario Veterinary College in 1996. She spent most of her her early career in Standardbred racing. She joined our practice in 2022 when she decided to try small animal practice full time. She has 3 cats and 3 horses which she shares with her husband. She likes to spend her free time with her horses or going on road trips.

members.name: Dr. C. Singh
members.title: Veterinarian
members.about: Dr. Singh earned his bachelors of veterinary sciences from KCVAS, Punjab India. He has a deep interest and passion for veterinary medicine and surgery. He loves to play with his dog Jenny. When he isn't working, he loves to spend his time reading and entertaining his friends and family. He likes learning something new every day.

members.name: Jennifer Pulvermacher
members.title: Clinic Manager
members.about: Jennifer is currently working as the Clinic Manager and is a certified Medical Office Assistant from Vancouver Island University. She has been a part of the team since Sept 2013. She has a passion for the well-being of animals and strives to give them the best care. She currently has 3 rowdy cats named Tux, Kitsy and Kaytan.

members.name: Tiffany Anderson
members.title: Registered Animal Health Technologist
members.about: Tiffany is currently working as an Animal Health Technologist. She has worked in small animal practices for over 10 years, and has been a Veterinary Technician for the last 6 months. She has worked at our clinic since March 2021. She shares her home with a loud and demanding cat named Lily.

members.title: Registered Animal Health Technologist
members.about: Sarah is currently working as a Registered Veterinary Technologist. She completed her AHT program at Olds College in 2022. She has 2 cats, Atlas and Ripley and her newest edition, Newton, an Australian Shepherd. She likes to spend her free time outdoors and travelling.
members.name: Sarah Woodcock
Jolene Janes
members.title: Veterinary Assistant
members.about: Jolene is currently working as a Veterinary Assistant. She has been at the clinic since 2017. She went to Olds College for her Veterinary Medical Reception certificate. She has a passion for animals and spends her time with her 2 cats (Kirby and Link) and at the dog park with her 2 super high-energy dogs (Skye and Ellie). She has 2 wonderful little boys that fill her life with joy.

members.title: Veterinary Assistant
members.name: Stephanie Rempel
members.about: Stephanie is full time mom of two beautiful daughters and is currently working as a Veterinary Assistant. She started out as a Health Care Aid, and then proceeded to further her education as a Medical Office Assistant before deciding to switch to Veterinary medicine. She loves to spend her time here at work with all of the animals, or at the dog park with her Chihuahua named Cali and her Blue Heeler named Akita.

members.name: Hope Woods
members.title: Veterinary Assistant
members.about: Hope is currently working as a Veterinary Assistant. She completed her Veterinary Office Assistant Certificate through Robertson College. She started at Taylor Veterinary Clinic in 2022. She has a German Shepherd/Borzoi Mix named Layla and two cats (Auto and Simone). She enjoys board games and movies.

members.name: Jessica Hurlburt
members.title: Veterinary Assistant
members.about: Jessica is currently working as a Veterinary Assistant. She wants to continue to work and expand her knowledge in the animal industry. She started working at Taylor Veterinary Clinic in August of 2023. She owns 5 cats (Alice, Zeppelin, Duncan, Archie and Lola). She enjoys spending time with loved ones, art, and gaming.

title: Our Team
intro: At Taylor Veterinary Clinic, we take pride in our team of veterinarians and staff, and recruit professional, energetic and enthusiastic associate veterinarians to join our clinic.
